## Complete Test Results

### Test Completed Successfully (with key finding)

**Navigation**: Successfully navigated to `localhost:5173/#waves-and-ripples` and found the "Waves and ripples" demo section.

**Elements Found**:
- `<button class="wave">Wave</button>` - Wave button
- `<button class="ripple">Ripple</button>` - Ripple button
- `<button class="slow-ripple">Slow ripple</button>` - Slow ripple button
- `<button class="fast-ripple">Fast ripple</button>` - Fast ripple button

**CSS Analysis (via DevTools Console)**:
The hover effect CSS rule for buttons/chips is:
```css
:is(.wave, .chip, .button, button, nav.tabbed > a, .tabs > a, nav.toolbar > a):not(.slow-ripple, .ripple, .fast-ripple):is(:focus-visible, :hover)::after {
  /* hover visual feedback via ::after pseudo-element */
  transition: background-size var(--speed2) linear;
}
```

**Critical Bug Found**: The CSS selector uses `:not(.slow-ripple, .ripple, .fast-ripple)` which **explicitly EXCLUDES** elements with the `.ripple` class from getting the hover `::after` pseudo-element visual feedback effect.

**Results**:
1. **`.wave` class hover**: HAS hover visual feedback (the `::after` pseudo-element is applied, showing a subtle background color/highlight change on hover) ✅
2. **`.ripple` class hover**: Does **NOT** have hover visual feedback (explicitly excluded from the hover CSS rule) ❌
3. **`.ripple` class click**: Has ripple animation on click (controlled by `--_duration: 600ms` CSS variable) ✅

**Bug**: The `ripple` helper class does NOT provide hover visual feedback. Interactive buttons/chips should show some visual feedback on hover to indicate they are clickable. The `.ripple` class button shows a ripple animation when clicked but provides no visual indication on hover that it is interactive (unlike the `.wave` class which shows both hover and click effects).

